title.narrative: Ministry of Public Works Institutional Strengthening TAL

description.narrative: The Project Development Objective is to assist the Government in achieving a sustainable and integrated approach to the planning of infrastructure; levels of service standards for infrastructure as well as model contracts and procedures that promote competition and assign risks appropriately; an integrated project management process; a regulatory framework for all of MOPW#s sectors of responsibility that increases consumer confidence in infrastructure service provision; and the legal and organizational separation of the areas of planning, contracting, execution and regulation of infrastructure provision.

title.narrative: Share of projects approved based on new integrated planning methodology.

comment.narrative: A new planning methodology is a key feature of the Modernization Program of the Ministry of PUblic Works

target.value: 25% of projects that initiate a phase of the project cycle (from prefeasibility to execution) adopted/initiated based on newplanning methodology

comment.narrative: See Key Issues and Actions for Management Attention

actual.value: 93% of projects to be executed using the new methodology (99% of the total investment)

title.narrative: Reduction in the variance of the difference between costs forecasted when contract is signed and actual cost of works

comment.narrative: Consulting firm being hired to prepare baseline. Note that more than 60 projects currently under integrated project management.

target.value: Reduction of 15% in the variance of cost deviations. Measured against baseline that will include only projects under integratedproject management

comment.narrative: See Key Issues and Actions for Management Attention

actual.value: Reduction of 14% of projects in 2012 using the new methodology.

comment.narrative: No information provided for 2013

title.narrative: Identify, define and adopt service quality standards in a wide set of works typologies under the responsibility of the MOPW

target.value: Service standards defined for 9 typology of works under the jurisdiction of MOPW

comment.narrative: See Key Issues and Actions for Management Attention

actual.value: Service standards defined for 13 typology of works under the jurisdiction of MOPW

comment.narrative: Identification of service quality attributes relevant, indicators and standards of service in the following 13 types of works(Airport Concession, Concession Road Works; jail concession; Lakeside Connectivity Project, Maritime and Fluvial Isolated Areas,Buildings MOP, Storm water; Rural Water, hospital). Standards included in performance based road maintenance contracts

title.narrative: More competition in biddings to be reached by (i) improvements in bidders registry (reglamento de obras y consultoria) and (ii) improved standard bidding documents

baseline.value: Bidding documents and firms and consultants registry currently in use by MOPW

target.value: 80% of contracts signed by MOPW during the year 2012 using new bidding documents. A third party, independent of MOPW to conduct anassessment of the impact of new bidding documents and improved "registro de contratistas" on intensity of competition

comment.narrative: See Key Issues and Actions for Management Attention

actual.value: Proposal to change contractors registry elaborated and under review by MOPW authorities. No progress in improved standard biddingdocuments

comment.narrative: Proposal to change contractors registry elaborated and under review by MOPW authorities. No progress in improved standard biddingdocuments

title.narrative: Number of concession contracts under the jurisdiction of the MOPW that incorporate (explicitly) quality standards

target.value: 7 contracts include, from bidding stage, explicit service standards

comment.narrative: See Key Issues and Actions for Management Attention
7 contracts in total – 2 contracts added in 2012 (inclusion of quality standards in bidding of Calama and Antofagasta airports)

title.narrative: A normative and organizational framework in place that provides for clear separation of roles and responsibilities

baseline.value: MOPW does not have an internal organization law that separates the roles of planning, implementation and supervision

target.value: Following laws approved by Congress: (i) New organizational structure of MOPW (ii) New concessions law (iii) Law that creates theSuperintendency of Public Works

comment.narrative: See Key Issues and Actions for Management Attention
Concession law approved as Law 20410 (January 2010). Law that creates the Superintendency in Congress but not a priority forcurrent administration

title.narrative: Regulatory oversight system in place to be used by entity independent of planning and execution divisionos of MOPW

baseline.value: No regulatory oversight system by an independent agency in place (currently done in house by MOPW personnel)

target.value: Regulatory oversight system and mechanisms in place for the following sectors: aiports concessions and inter and urban roadsconcessions.

comment.narrative: See Key Issues and Actions for Management Attention

actual.value: 3 web based systems put in place

comment.narrative: Implementation of web based system to oversight and report concessions (roads, airports, water).

title.narrative: Reduction of variance of construction time between time envisaged when contract is signed and actual construction time

comment.narrative: % reduction in indicator (variance).See attached document discussing some issues and possible solutions for PDO and intermediateresult indicators.
19% time reduction to the projects implemented using the new methodology (GIP) finished in year 2011. There is no update for 2013

title.narrative: Increased return of infrastructure projects due to the new planning methodology

comment.narrative: See Key Issues and Actions for Management Attention
Indicator was changed in 2009

title.narrative: Reduction in variance between values established at contract signature and final values at project execution

target.value: eduction of 15% in the variance of cost deviations. Measured against baseline that will include only projects under integratedproject management

comment.narrative: See attached document discussing some issues and possible solutions for PDO and intermediate result indicators.

actual.value: Reduction of 14% of projects in 2012 using the new methodology.

comment.narrative: No information provided for 2013

title.narrative: Normative and organizational structure that provides clear separation and definition of roles and responsibilities for planning, contracting, works execution and oversight.

comment.narrative: See Key Issues and Actions for Management Attention

actual.value: Concession law approved as Law 20410 (January 2010). Law that creates the Superintendency in Congress but not a priority forcurrent administration.Significant progress in the monitoring of road concessions. Regulatory oversight system being applied to 20interurban road concession contracts and 6 urban road concession contracts. Web based system

title.narrative: Greater responsiveness to consumer concerns related to levels of service; and greater oversight of performance by public sector service providers as well as concessionaires

comment.narrative: See Key Issues and Actions for Management Attention

actual.value: Service standards defined for 13 typology of works under the jurisdiction of MOPW.MPW developed a system to assess users’satisfaction for concessioned / publicly administrated inter-urban roads, urban roads (concessioned), airports (concessioned),connectivity, and jails. In 2012 the MPW measured the level of satisfaction of many roads (inter-urban, urban), and airports.

title.narrative: Greater competition in bidding supported by fair risk-sharing arrangements embedded in contracts and consumer-responsive service targets

comment.narrative: See Key Issues and Actions for Management Attention
